Title: CryptoManager++ An Object Oriented Class Library for Cryptographic Mechanisms  
Author: Thilo Baldin, Gerrit Bleumer 
Keyword: Security API, cryptographic mechanisms, hybrid mechanisms, object oriented, class hierarchy  
Affiliation: Department of Computing, University of Hildesheim  
Abstract: This paper describes the general concepts of an object oriented class library for cryptographic mechanisms: CryptoManager++. Its application programming interface (API) provides security services of various symmetric and asymmetric cryptographic mechanisms. Nevertheless, these services can be used in an uniform and convenient way achieved by means of object oriented techniques such as inheritance and overloading. Es - pecially, the provided services include cooperations of several cryptographic mechanisms (like e.g. hybrid encryption), allowing to treat such a cooperation as one (integrated) mechanism at the API. Further main design principles were easy integration of new mechanisms, individually adjustable security, support of bit stream operands, portability and efficiency. The implementation of the CryptoManager++ is done almost completely in C++. 
